Sentencas: In this study, the interactions of a Sr- and Mg-doped lanthanum gallate (LSGM with composition La0.9Sr0.1 Ga0.8Mg0.2Odelta) electrolyte with Fe2O3, Co2O3 and NiO as the anode starting materials were investigated.
Titulo: Interactions of a La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte with Fe2O3, Co2O3 and NiO anode materials

Sentencas: It was found that the older of reactivity of the LSGM with the three oxides was Co2O3 > NiO > Fe2O3, and La-containing oxides were detected in these binary powder mixtures after firing.
Titulo: Interactions of a La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte with Fe2O3, Co2O3 and NiO anode materials

Sentencas: The anode performance was greatly influenced by the interaction.
Titulo: Interactions of a La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte with Fe2O3, Co2O3 and NiO anode materials

Sentencas: The Fe2O3-LSGM anode, mixed with 40 vol.% LSGM powder and sintered at 1150 degreesC, exhibited the highest initial performance in comparison with NiO-LSGM and Co2O3-LSGM anodes.
Titulo: Interactions of a La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte with Fe2O3, Co2O3 and NiO anode materials

Sentencas: It seems that Fe2O3 is a possible anode starting material for a LSGM-based solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Interactions of a La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte with Fe2O3, Co2O3 and NiO anode materials
